The steering doc is now live at 
expense-tracker.md
 and will be automatically included in every future session with this workspace. Kiro will use it as context for all decisions — new features, bug fixes, refactors — without you needing to re-explain the app's design.

A few things worth noting about what's captured:

The legacy DB compatibility section (§4.1/4.2, §11) is particularly important — it documents the dual-write requirement for created_at/created_date that caused the sub-expense insert bug, so that pattern won't be repeated if the schema evolves again
The category list (§5) is the canonical reference — any future addition of a category needs to be updated here, in both the backend SUB_EXPENSE_CATEGORIES list, and the two frontend CATEGORY_META objects
The card rendering pattern (§8.5) and bulk save decision (§11) capture the non-obvious architectural choices that would be easy to get wrong when adding new features
If you add significant new features going forward, just ask to update the steering doc and it'll stay current.